The paper deals with the dynamic streaming setting for the $k$-means clustering problem, which involves updating the dataset with new points and deleting existing points. This suggests that the paper could belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) category. Additionally, the paper proposes a coreset construction algorithm for the $k$-means problem, which involves finding a smaller set of points that approximately preserves the clustering structure of the original dataset. This suggests that the paper could also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) category. The paper also deals with high-dimensional data, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) category. Finally, the paper deals with the $k$-means clustering problem, which is a common problem in the fields of databases and artificial intelligence, suggesting that it could belong to the cs.DB (Databases) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) categories.
